"iniquity":{
  word:"iniquity",plain:"Twisted, bent moral disorder — the warp that sin leaves in the person.",
  deep:"Hebrew AVON (H5771, root AVAH — to bend, twist) names sin as crookedness — the moral deformity that follows wrongdoing. Often distinguished from PESHA (rebellion) and CHATAT (missing the mark) — Ex 34:7 lists all three. Greek ANOMIA (G458, 'lawlessness') and ADIKIA (G93, 'unrighteousness') translate the family in NT.",
  misunderstood:"Treating 'iniquity' as a synonym for 'sin' generally loses the specific picture of bent, twisted moral shape.",
  matters:"Isa 53:5 — 'bruised for our iniquities' — Christ bears the twistedness, not merely the acts.",
  originals:[{lang:"Hebrew",word:"עָוֹן",translit:"avon",strongs:"H5771",note:"Iniquity, twistedness, guilt."},{lang:"Greek",word:"ἀνομία",translit:"anomia",strongs:"G458",note:"Lawlessness."},{lang:"Greek",word:"ἀδικία",translit:"adikia",strongs:"G93",note:"Unrighteousness."}],
  rangeOfMeaning:["twistedness","guilt","punishment for twistedness"],notMean:"Not undifferentiated 'sin.'",
  cultural:"ANE moral language pictured sin as crookedness vs. uprightness.",
  kingdomSignificance:"Christ removes iniquity (Isa 53; Heb 8:12) — straightens what was bent.",
  relatedVerses:["Exodus 34:7","Psalm 32:5","Psalm 51:2-9","Isaiah 53:5-6","Jeremiah 31:34","Matthew 7:23","Romans 4:7","Hebrews 8:12","1 John 3:4"],
  relatedWords:["sin","transgression","trespass","lawlessness"],category:"sin / judgment",
  sources:["Strong's H5771","Strong's G458","Strong's G93","BDB","Thayer's"],confidence:"direct-source"
},
