  deep:"Hebrew PESHA (H6588, verb PASHA H6586) — to rebel, break covenant. Stronger than 'mistake' — names defiance. Greek PARABASIS (G3847) — overstepping; PARAPTOMA (G3900) — false step, trespass.",
  misunderstood:"Soft modern use ('I transgressed the speed limit'); biblical force = covenant rebellion.",
