  word:"begat",plain:"Fathered / became the father of — the keyword of biblical genealogies.",
  deep:"Hebrew YALAD (H3205, qal/hiphil) — to bear, beget. Greek GENNAO (G1080). Begat-language structures Gen 5, Gen 10, Gen 11, 1 Chr 1-9, Matt 1, Luke 3. Spiritually applied: 'born of God' / 'begotten of God' (John 1:13; 1 John 5:1).",
  misunderstood:"Modern readers skip the begats and miss covenant lineage. Matt 1 and Luke 3 anchor Jesus in Abraham, David, and Adam.",
